<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10141</anchor> <rss>erct-0025.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0025</addr>  <route>erct-0025.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Retract</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0025.agda" type="external">erct-0025.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>When <tex>s \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>, we say that <tex>A</tex> is a <em><strong>retract</strong></em> of <tex>B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10142</anchor> <rss>erct-000Z.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-000Z</addr>  <route>erct-000Z.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Functions and inverses</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10143</anchor> <rss>erct-001Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001Q</addr>  <route>erct-001Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Q.agda" type="external">erct-001Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> at an element <tex>b:B</tex> is the type consisting of elements <tex>a \colon  A</tex> equipped with identifications <tex>p \colon  fa=b</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10144</anchor> <rss>erct-0014.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0014</addr>  <route>erct-0014.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Homotopy</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0014.agda" type="external">erct-0014.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f , g  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> be two dependent functions. A <em><strong>homotopy</strong></em> from <tex>f</tex> to <tex>g</tex>, writing <tex>H \colon  f  \sim  g</tex> is given by a dependent function <tex>H \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } fx=gx</tex>. We shall write <tex>1_{ f } \colon  f  \sim  f</tex> for the <em><strong>identity homotopy</strong></em> on <tex>f</tex> defined by <tex>1_{ f } x: \equiv   \mathsf {refl}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10145</anchor> <rss>erct-001V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001V</addr>  <route>erct-001V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Naturality of <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopies</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001V.agda" type="external">erct-001V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>H  \colon  f  \sim  g</tex> be a <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> between two functions <tex>f,g \colon  A  \to  B</tex>. For any identification <tex>p \colon  x =y</tex> in <tex>A</tex>, we have an identification <tex>H x  \cdot   \mathsf {ap}_{ g } \, p =  \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \, p \cdot  Hy</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10146</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By identification induction on <tex>p</tex>, it suffices to show that <tex>Hx \cdot \mathsf {refl}  =  \mathsf {refl} \cdot  Hx</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10147</anchor> <rss>erct-001W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001W</addr>  <route>erct-001W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Naturality of <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopies</link> onto the identity</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001W.agda" type="external">erct-001W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>H  \colon  f  \sim   1_{ A }</tex> be a <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> from <tex>f \colon  A  \to  A</tex> onto the identity function. Then we may construct a higher homotopy from <tex>H \circ  f</tex> to <tex>\mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ  H</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10148</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Fixing <tex>x:A</tex>, we must construct an identification from <tex>H \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> to <tex>\mathsf {ap}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. By the naturality (<ref addr="erct-001V" href="erct-001V.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>) of <tex>H</tex> at the identification <tex>H x \colon  f x = x</tex>, we have an identification <tex>H \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}   \cdot   \mathsf {ap}_{ 1_{ A } } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  H x</tex>.</p>
 <p>Simplifying, we have <tex>H \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  H x =  \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  H x</tex>; canceling <tex>H x</tex> on either side, we therefore have the desired identification <tex>H \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( H x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10149</anchor> <rss>erct-000Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr>  <route>erct-000Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Section-retraction pair</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>. Together, <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( s,r \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> are referred to as a <em><strong>section-retraction pair</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10150</anchor> <rss>erct-0025.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0025</addr>  <route>erct-0025.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Retract</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0025.agda" type="external">erct-0025.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>When <tex>s \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>, we say that <tex>A</tex> is a <em><strong>retract</strong></em> of <tex>B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10151</anchor> <rss>erct-000U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr>  <route>erct-000U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10152</anchor> <rss>erct-000X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000X</addr>  <route>erct-000X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Quasi-inverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>quasi-inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a function <tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> equipped with homotopies <tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, rendering <tex>g</tex> simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p><p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <tex>\eta</tex> and <tex>\epsilon</tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <em>unit</em> and <em>counit</em> of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10153</anchor> <rss>erct-000W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr>  <route>erct-000W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10154</anchor> <rss>erct-000V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000V</addr>  <route>erct-000V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Equivalence of types</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000V.agda" type="external">erct-000V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>equivalence</strong></em> from <tex>A</tex> to <tex>B</tex> is defined to be a function <tex>A  \to  B</tex> equipped with a  <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverse</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10155</anchor> <rss>erct-003C.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-003C</addr>  <route>erct-003C.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link> to <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003C.agda" type="external">erct-003C.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10156</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to <tex>f</tex> is simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10157</anchor> <rss>erct-002C.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002C</addr>  <route>erct-002C.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link> to coherent <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverses</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002C.agda" type="external">erct-002C.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> have a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> <tex>g \colon  B \to  A</tex> with incoherent counit <tex>\epsilon \colon  f \circ  g \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and unit <tex>\eta \colon  g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex>. We can <em>correct</em> the counit to obtain a coherent <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> to <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10158</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The corrected counit <tex>\epsilon '  \colon  g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> is defined like so:</p>
 <tex display="block">
   \epsilon ' x : \equiv 
   \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( f \mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} ^{-1}   \cdot   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta \mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {}   \cdot   \epsilon  x
 </tex>

 <p>The coherence <tex>\chi \colon   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon ' \circ  f</tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmata <ref addr="erct-001V" href="erct-001V.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001W" href="erct-001W.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10159</anchor> <rss>erct-002D.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002D</addr>  <route>erct-002D.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link> to <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002D.agda" type="external">erct-002D.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> with <tex>s,r \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>h_s \colon  f  \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>h_r \colon  r \circ  f =  1_{ A }</tex>. Then we may define a homotopy <tex>h'  \colon  s \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A }</tex> exhibiting <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> as a retraction of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>. Therefore, we may define a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to <tex>f</tex> tracked by <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10160</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We have <tex>s \circ  f  \sim  r \circ  f  \circ  s \circ  f</tex> by <tex>h_r</tex> and <tex>r \circ  f  \circ  s \circ  f \sim  r  \circ  f</tex> by <tex>h_s</tex> and <tex>r \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A }</tex> by <tex>h_r</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10161</anchor> <rss>erct-002I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002I</addr>  <route>erct-002I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002I.agda" type="external">erct-002I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be maps equipped with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> <tex>s_f \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>s_g \colon  C \to  B</tex>. The composite <tex>s_f \circ  s_g \colon  C \to  A</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10162</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>The witness of sectionhood is defined using the witnesses for the two sections.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10163</anchor> <rss>erct-002J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002J</addr>  <route>erct-002J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002J.agda" type="external">erct-002J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be maps equipped with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> <tex>r_f \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>r_g \colon  C \to  B</tex>. The composite <tex>r_f \circ  r_g \colon  C \to  A</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10164</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The witness of retractionhood is defined using the witnesses for the two retractions.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10165</anchor> <rss>erct-002K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002K</addr>  <route>erct-002K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002K.agda" type="external">erct-002K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>, with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections and retractions</link> given by <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10166</anchor> <rss>erct-002L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002L</addr>  <route>erct-002L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002L.agda" type="external">erct-002L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is quasi-invertible, with sectionhood and retractionhood witnesses given by those of the <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10167</anchor> <rss>erct-003J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-003J</addr>  <route>erct-003J.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverses</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003J.agda" type="external">erct-003J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A \to  C</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10168</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002C" href="erct-002C.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to find a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to the composite <tex>g \circ  f</tex>; we take this to be the composite (<ref addr="erct-002L" href="erct-002L.xml" taxon="Construction"/>) of the underlying <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link> of <tex>f</tex> and <tex>g</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10169</anchor> <rss>erct-002Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Q</addr>  <route>erct-002Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Sections</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> are unique</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Q.agda" type="external">erct-002Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of some <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10170</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002Q</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</link>, we can see that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex>, using the <link href="erct-0023.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0023" title="The univalence principle for sections">univalence principle for sections</link>.</p>

 <p>To show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> already, we know that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">therefore</link> that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>. Because <link href="erct-0026.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0026" title="Propositions are closed under retracts">propositions are closed under retracts</link>, it suffices to show that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, which <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">follows</link> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10171</anchor> <rss>erct-002R.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002R</addr>  <route>erct-002R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Retractions</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> are unique</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002R.agda" type="external">erct-002R.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of some <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10172</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002R</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Analogous to the <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002Q" title="Sections of sections are unique">corresponding result for sections of sections</link>, using the fact that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> can be seen to be a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>- \circ  f</tex> at <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10173</anchor> <rss>erct-0026.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0026</addr>  <route>erct-0026.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0026.agda" type="external">erct-0026.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>B</tex> and <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10174</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-0026</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This can be seen using the cancellation laws of retractions.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10175</anchor> <rss>erct-0027.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0027</addr>  <route>erct-0027.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">Contractible</link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0027.agda" type="external">erct-0027.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>B</tex> and <tex>B</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>, then <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10176</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-0027</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>s \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; if <tex>b_0</tex> is the centre of contraction of <tex>B</tex>, then the centre of contraction of <tex>A</tex> is given by <tex>rb_0</tex>. For the rest, we use the fact that <link href="erct-0026.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0026" title="Propositions are closed under retracts">propositions are closed under retracts</link> and <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>